

A total of 3,640 patients with signs and symptoms similar to dengue fever have been admitted to different hospitals across Pakistan by Thursday evening, said a press statement from the ministry of health.

About 1,410 patients have been found positive for dengue fever all over the country by Thursday, the statement said.

There has been a total of 37 deaths from the disease, of which 35 were reported from the Sindh province while two were from North West Frontier Province (NWFP). No death has been reported so far from other parts of the country.

A total of 559 patients were admitted to different hospitals of Islamabad and Rawalpindi with signs and symptoms similar to dengue fever.

By Thursday evening the total number of positive cases in Islamabad and Rawalpindi stood at 197, according to the statement.

